The paper focuses on improving the performance of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) through image augmentation techniques. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also introduces new techniques for augmentation, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the experiments are conducted on the CIFAR-10 dataset, which is commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
